cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with anomaly detection in images, which is a computer vision problem, hence cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a deep learning approach using disentangled learning, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper also mentions the use of bounding intervals, which is a technique used in neural networks, hence cs.NE is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on three datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia analysis, hence cs.MM is also a possible sub-category.
